The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 06 October is 78,750 (9,076.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 01 October, there were 2,540 new confirmed cases (292.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 24 September, there were 2,225 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 14% (315 extra cases).
